Received on: 2018-07-23<p/> Description: Red / White<p/>  Neutered Male Pit Bull Dog<p/> Age: 8 YEARS 1 MONTH<p/> Current Location: King County Pet Adoption Center 21615 64TH AVE S KENT, WA 98032<p/>Hi! My name is Bruno and I am available for adoption.<p/><p/>I was brought in by a good samaritan on July 23, 2018.<p/><p/>When I first arrived at the shelter I was very scared and nervous. You may noticed I'm a big dog, but I really am more of a big baby. My history is unknown to the shelter since I arrived as a stray, but my caregivers have noticed that I need time and patience to adjust to my surroundings and my people friends.<p/><p/>Once I get to know people, I do enjoy company, but I am not an overly touchy guy. I appreciate a few pets here and there but I have an image to maintain so I do best without a lot of cuddles. This may change with time, but for now I appreciate you respecting my space and giving my attention when I ask for it. I don't want to be doted over.<p/><p/>While I might not be the best fit as a snuggle buddy, I do love to play! Toys are my best frienda! I tend to calm down more when the people around me stay calm. I do best when I have lots of exercise and something to keep my mind busy.<p/><p/>Because of my weary nature and sensitivity to handling, I would do best in a dog savvy home with adults only.<p/><p/>My caregivers have noticed that I seem to do well with other dogs. I may do best as the only pet in my new home.<p/><p/>My personality color is RED. I am a spirited dog with a fun-loving personality! I am still working on my manners, so I would do best with a family who is willing to work with me and help me become the best dog I can be!<p/> Adoption Fee: $100.00<p/>
